  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Select Medical?",
  "response": "Congratulations on your new role at Select Medical! Here are some things that might be helpful to know going into your first day:\n\n### Company Overview\n- **Select Medical** is a healthcare company focused on providing niche medical services across the United States. They operate specialty hospitals, inpatient rehabilitation, outpatient rehabilitation clinics, and occupational medicine centers.\n  \n### Company Values and Culture\n- **Mission and Values**: Understand Select Medical\u2019s mission and core values, which often emphasize patient-centered care, teamwork, and clinical excellence.\n- **Work Environment**: Be prepared for a collaborative and supportive work culture. Building relationships with colleagues is important.\n\n### Policies and Procedures\n- **Dress Code**: Confirm the required dress code. Healthcare settings often require professional attire or uniforms.\n- **Compliance**: Be aware of compliance policies related to patient confidentiality, medical records, and healthcare regulations. HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) knowledge is crucial.\n- **Safety Procedures**: Familiarize yourself with the workplace safety protocols, especially if you are working in clinical settings.\n\n### Training and Onboarding\n- **Orientation**: Expect to undergo orientation sessions that will introduce you to company policies, procedures, and systems.\n- **Training Programs**: You'll likely receive training tailored to your role. This may include computer systems, patient care protocols, or administrative processes.\n\n### Day-to-Day Operations\n- **Patient Interaction**: If you are in a clinical role, patient care is central. Understand the patient flow and the importance of empathy and professionalism.\n- **Team Collaboration**: Work closely with your team. Effective communication and collaboration are essential.\n- **Technology**: Familiarize yourself with the electronic health record (EHR) systems and other technologies used in your department.\n\n### Professional Development\n- **Continuing Education**: Select Medical often offers opportunities for ongoing training and professional development. Take advantage of these resources.\n- **Career Pathways**: Explore various career advancement opportunities within the company.\n\n### Logistics\n- **Location and Parking**: Ensure you know how to get to your specific location and where parking is available.\n- **Time Management**: Arrive early to give yourself time to settle in and start the day smoothly.\n\n### Support and Resources\n- **HR Support**: Know how to access HR resources for any questions about benefits, payroll, or policies.\n- **Mentorship**: Seek out a mentor or key contact for any guidance and support during your initial days.\n\n### Miscellaneous Tips\n- **Positive Attitude**: Bring a positive and proactive attitude. First impressions matter, and showing enthusiasm can set a good tone.\n- **Questions and Curiosity**: Don\u2019t hesitate to ask questions. It\u2019s better to seek clarification than to assume.\n\nBest of luck on your first day and in your new role at Select Medical!",
